<i>adverb</i>: 절대 [절때], 일절 [일쩔], 온전히 [온ː전히], 영 [영], 어련히 [어련히] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square"><li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>절대 [절때]</dt><br>
<dd>absolutely; never</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 경우라도 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>Surely and in any case.</dd><br>
<dt>일절 [일쩔]</dt><br>
<dd>never; absolutely</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 있어도 꼭. 또는 이러니저러니 할 것 없이 아주.</dd><br>
<dd>In any case; without exception.</dd><br>
<dt>온전히 [온ː전히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. soundly; wholly</dd><br>
<dd>본래의 모습 그대로 고스란히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of something being intact as it originally was.</dd><br>
<dd>2. perfectly; absolutely</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 것이 없이 완벽하거나 올바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a perfect or accurate manner without any flaw.</dd><br>
<dt>영 [영]</dt><br>
<dd>1. not in the least</dd><br>
<dd>전혀 또는 도무지.</dd><br>
<dd>Never or not at all.</dd><br>
<dd>2. totally; absolutely; entirely</dd><br>
<dd>아주 또는 완전히.</dd><br>
<dd>Quite or completely.</dd><br>
<dt>어련히 [어련히]</dt><br>
<dd>definitely; certainly; absolutely</dd><br>
<dd>걱정하지 않아도 될 만큼 잘될 것이 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a definite manner in which there is no need to worry because things will turn out fine.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>